| Feature           | CSS Selector                                | XPath                                            |
| ----------------- | ------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------ |
| **Language Type** | CSS based syntax                            | XML path language                                |
| **Performance**   | Faster than XPath                           | Slightly slower                                  |
| **Direction**     | Only **forward direction** (parent → child) | Both **forward and backward** (parent ↔ child)   |
| **Syntax**        | Simple aur short                            | Thoda complex                                    |
| **Traversing**    | Parent se child locate kar sakte hain       | Parent, child, sibling sab locate kar sakte hain |
| **Text Handling** | Direct text search possible nahi            | Text search possible hai                         |
| **Usage**         | Mostly preferred for speed                  | Complex elements locate karne ke liye            |


CSS Selector is generally faster and uses CSS syntax to locate elements, but it only supports forward traversal in the DOM. XPath is 
more powerful because
it allows both forward and backward traversal and can locate elements using text and complex relationships.
